[[sn:Kamuna&#39;obi]] [[en:Kamuna&#39;obi]] [[ja:神直日神]]
==Merged second translation== [[Image:Descendants of izanagi alone.svg|thumb|right|200px|Deities born from Izanagi's purification (based on the Kojiki) [//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d3/Creation_myths_of_Japan_5.svg View in SVG (supported browsers only)]]]] '''Kamunaobi no Kami''' (神直日神, also spelled かむなおひのかみ) is a deity in {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto|qq=}}.<ref name="T">[[Atsushi Yamakita]] 『東洋神名事典』 [[Gakken]] p. 349.</ref> This deity is said to purify defilements and rectify {{ill|Magatsuhi|ja|禍|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Magatsuhi|qq=}} (misfortunes or evils). In the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kojiki|qq=}}, the deity is referred to as Kamunaobi no Kami (神直毘神), while the {{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Shoki|qq=}} refers to the deity as Kamunaohi no Kami (神直日神). Other texts also spell the name as Kamunaobi no Kami (神直備神).
== Overview == During the {{ill|Birth of the Gods|ja|神産み|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Birth of the Gods|qq=}}, {{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊邪那岐命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanagi|qq=}} returned from {{ill|Yomi|ja|黄泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yomi|qq=}}, where defilements from Yomi gave rise to {{ill|Magatsuhi no Kami|ja|禍津日神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Magatsuhi no Kami|qq=}}. To counteract the calamities caused by Magatsuhi no Kami, Kamunaobi no Kami was born as one of the {{ill|Naobi no Kami|ja|直毘神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naobi no Kami|qq=}}. Subsequently, another deity, {{ill|Ōnaobi no Kami|ja|大直毘神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōnaobi no Kami|qq=}}, was born, followed by {{ill|Izunome|ja|伊豆能売|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izunome|qq=}}.
== Historical Interpretations == According to {{ill|Shinobu Orikuchi|ja|折口信夫|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinobu Orikuchi|qq=}}, Kamunaobi no Kami has the following attributes:<ref name="U">[[Shinobu Orikuchi]] 『折口信夫全集 新版』 [[Chūōkōron-sha]].</ref> * Naobi no Kami is considered a paired and interconnected deity with Magatsuhi no Kami, embodying their dual aspects. Additionally, Kamunaobi no Kami functions as the officiant deity in purification rituals, while Izunome is considered the miko (shrine maiden). * The term "naoru" (to rectify or correct) is linguistically related to the "Nao" (直) in Kamunaobi no Kami, implying a deity invoked to rectify missteps or wrongdoings. * By the Heian period, Kamunaobi no Kami was associated with being a deity of feasts or entertainment.
== Major Shrines Dedicated to Kamunaobi no Kami and Ōnaobi no Kami == * {{ill|Kego Shrine|ja|警固神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kego Shrine|qq=}}, Fukuoka City, Fukuoka Prefecture * {{ill|Sakurai Shrine (Itoshima)|ja|桜井神社 (糸島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakurai Shrine (Itoshima)|qq=}}, Itoshima City, Fukuoka Prefecture * Naobi Shrine, Nogata City, Fukuoka Prefecture * {{ill|Hayasuhime Shrine|ja|早吸日女神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayasuhime Shrine|qq=}}, Ōita City, Ōita Prefecture * {{ill|Sasamuta Shrine|ja|西寒多神社|1=Sasamuta Shrine|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasamuta Shrine|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasamuta Shrine|qq=}}, Ōita City, Ōita Prefecture * {{ill|Dewa Shrine|ja|出羽神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dewa Shrine|qq=}} (Ōnaobi Shrine on the grounds), Tsuruoka City, Yamagata Prefecture * Gosen Hachiman Shrine, Gosen City, Niigata Prefecture * {{ill|Udo Shrine|ja|鵜戸神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Udo Shrine|qq=}} (Kyuhashira Shrine on the grounds), Nichinan City, Miyazaki Prefecture * Isono Sata Shrine, Yazu District, Tottori Prefecture * Ōhara Shrine (Sakurai Shrine on the grounds), Ōnan Town, Shimane Prefecture * Noma Shrine, Imabari City, Ehime Prefecture * Kanbe Shrine, Kōshū City, Yamanashi Prefecture * Ōagata Shrine (Kaijo Shrine on the grounds), Inuyama City, Aichi Prefecture * {{ill|Zama Shrine|ja|坐摩神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zama Shrine|qq=}} (Aiden Shrine on the grounds), Osaka City, Osaka Prefecture * Ikuta Shrine, Toyooka City, Hyōgo Prefecture * {{ill|Ayatokunaka Shrine|ja|綾戸国中神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ayatokunaka Shrine|qq=}}, Kyoto City, Kyoto Prefecture * {{ill|Itsukushima Shrine|ja|厳島神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itsukushima Shrine|qq=}}, Hatsukaichi City, Hiroshima Prefecture * {{ill|Isonokami Shrine|ja|石上神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isonokami Shrine|qq=}} (Nanaza Shrine on the grounds), Tenri City, Nara Prefecture
