== Historical Interpretations == According to [[:en:Shinobu Orikuchi|Shinobu Orikuchi]], Kamunaobi no Kami has the following attributes:<ref name="U">[[Shinobu Orikuchi]] 『折口信夫全集 新版』 [[:en:Chūōkōron-sha|Chūōkōron-sha]].</ref> * Naobi no Kami is considered a paired and interconnected deity with Magatsuhi no Kami, embodying their dual aspects. Additionally, Kamunaobi no Kami functions as the officiant deity in purification rituals, while Izunome is considered the miko (shrine maiden). * The term "naoru" (to rectify or correct) is linguistically related to the "Nao" (直) in Kamunaobi no Kami, implying a deity invoked to rectify missteps or wrongdoings. * By the Heian period, Kamunaobi no Kami was associated with being a deity of feasts or entertainment.
